description: A radio show featuring interviews with local and international Salsa dancers and musicians, the history of Salsa music and dance and lots of great Salsa music!

Looking for fresh outfits to wear dancing? Let's raid each others' giveaway piles this Sunday during the SwingSoul party! This swap is intended for womens' clothes only. Here's how it works: 1. Put aside a pile of (clean) clothes that no longer bring you joy, BUT ARE DANCEABLE. 2. Bring your bag of DANCEABLE contributions with you when you come to SwingSoul on Sunday. Leave it with us to sort in the studio lobby, ideally before 8pm or shortly after. 3. Swap will start at 8pm (after the classes end) 4. Then you can browse around, try things on, and take whatever inspires you! Suggestions: T-shirts, blouses, tanks, sweaters, jeans, leggings, slacks, dance shoes clothes for dancing WCS! Don't bring this time: street shoes, coats, dresses, skirts, jewellery, men's clothing. (Maybe at a later date) We hope you join us for this opportunity to refresh your Westie wardrobe!
source: Vancouver West Coast Swing Community | Facebook

event_name: Intermediate Blues Dance Series: 1) Pulse & Groove, 2) Slow Drag, 3) Connection, 4) Musicality
description: This is the second run of our intermediate blues lesson series. Same topics as the previous intermediate series, but you're likely to get a little something different every time. Classes will ideally build on each other, but you do not necessarily have complete earlier ones to take the next. Single day drop-ins allowed, but please still send me a message. At least some prior blues dance experience is required. If you have less experience, please consider taking classes in order (especially pulse & groove first). 7:30-9pm Monday nights June. 2, 9, 16, 23 Instructors: Sara Sloan & Candra Marr. $20 per class (cash or e-transfer), $80 for series. Message me (Sara Sloan) to register ahead of time to get the exact address. Please let me know if you need to cancel asap, so I can open up more spots if needed. Due to the small space, I am limiting it to 10 participants. Topics: June 2: Pulse and Groove How to look and feel like a Blues pro. What makes Blues dance look like Blues dance and how do I make my movements feel bluesy? How to connect with your partner with different types of pulses. June 9: Slow Drag All about dancing slow and close embrace. The subtlety, connection and squish. June 16: Connection Blues has a flexibility of connection that allows for more individuality, but how do we stay connected even when we're doing different movements? June 23: Musicality There are as many styles of blues dance as there are styles of blues musichow do I know what styles to dance to this song? Listening, call and response, hitting the breaks - bringing the music and our partner together.
source: Vancouver West Coast Swing Community | Facebook
location: Marpole, Vancouver
price: $20 per class (cash or e-transfer), $80 for series

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description

description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Calienteâ€™s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST

description: Classically trained in ballet and modern dance, Amanda is known for her precise technique, artistry, and fluidity of movement. She has trained with notable artists such as Karen Kain, Veronica Tennant, and Alonzo King Lines Ballet, winning several awards, grants, and scholarships nationally. Her repertoire has expanded to include lyrical, contemporary, Argentine tango, flamenco, Chinese classical dancing, commercial styles, jazz, hip hop, ballroom, Latin, and salsa dance while keeping true to her first love of ballet. A professional dancer, dance teacher, choreographer and lover of all things movement-related, Amanda has worked in music videos, television commercials, and Bollywood movies and has also volunteered as a principal dancer and choreographer for Brilliant! Shine! and Red galas benefiting mental health and health research. Amanda teaches at Harbour Dance and the University of British Columbia and is on the Canadian Alliance of Dance Artists (CADA) Board of Directors. Amanda feels fortunate to be able to share her passion for dance with diverse audiences and arts lovers.
source: 2025 ARThritis SoirÃ©e Entertainment - Arthritis Research Canada

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Saanich Parks & Public Works Yard Tour
description: Join the Fun at the Saanich Parks & Public Works Yard Tour! This free event is open to all ages! Celebrate National Public Works Week with us by touring the home of our parks and public works teams! Our expert staff will guide you through engaging, interactive stations, sharing stories and insights on how they serve our community everyday. Try some of our coolest tools designed to keep our streets clean and safe! Get up close and personal with our traffic lights and giant underground pipes! Whether you're a long-time resident or new to the area, everyone will leave with a deeper understanding and appreciation of the services Saanich professionals provide. No registration is required - just bring your curiosity! We only open our doors once a year for this kind of event, and it's a memorable experience for all ages!
source: Line Dancing in Victoria, British Columbia, Canada: Joe & Cindy ...
location: 1040 McKenzie AVE, VICTORIA, BC, V8P2L4, CA

description: Specialized Workshops for Swing & Jazz Dancers! Lisa Marks: focus on spins and turns for your Lindy hop and Solo Jazz. Great for working on balance, posture, and grounded connection, too. All levels. Doug Barber: Solo Jazz Essentials for all Swing dancers. This is a great opportunity to learn/re-learn some basic Jazz steps; but more than that itâ€™s a chance to dive into connecting with the music and finding your own expression in movement. Lindsay Leong: Solo Jazz for experienced dancers â€“ Improvising with Musicality & Rhythm: Defining the Melody & the Fills. Students should have a solid foundation in basic jazz steps, can easily dance the Tranky-doo/Big Apple/other routines (besides the Shim Sham), and are willing to solo jam and sing (mezzo forte!) with their classmates. Lucy Falkner & Lindsay Leong: Lindy Hop for experienced dancers â€“ Students should have completed at least a few Intermediate sessions and/or be in the Team program. We will challenge your connection and improvisation skills with a complex combination; practice will include working your own variations and improvisations into the combination. (â€œCombinationâ€ = a 32-bar / 4 x 8-count sequence of moves.) The day starts with a dance warm-up/workout with Lucy. This hour will include stretches, cardio, footwork drills, core work, and bodyweight resistance work. The first half hour is for everyone of moderate fitness; the second half hour is for those who want a challenge.
source: Strictly Lindy Hop Swing Vancouver, BC
location: St Michaelâ€™s Hall, 2474 Prince Edward St, Vancouver, BC, Canada, British Columbia V5T 1W8

event_name: Savoy Night with DJ Vee at Rhythm City Strut
description: This week to commemorate the anniversary of 'the World's Finest Ballroom' DJ Vee (Vanessa Tara) plays the music of the Savoy house bands, from Chick Webb and Ella Fitzgerald to Fletcher Henderson, Erskine Hawkins, Benny Carter and many more. The Savoy opened on March 12, 1926, taking an entire city block on Lennox Avenue between 140th and 141st Streets. It could hold up to 4000 people (!!!) and was the home of New York's finest dancers and bands until it closed in 1958. ADMISSION FREE for all current Swing 1, Swing 2, Queer Intro To Swing and ELEF Intro To Swing students. $5 for all other RCP and UBC Swing Club students. Free admission if you've never danced before - bring your non-dance friends and we'll show them the basics! No one turned away for lack of funds. Message us or sign up for a volunteer shift at the door! Remember to bring your own water bottle. Be considerate of othersâ€™ decision to mask or not, and be prepared to put on a mask as a courtesy to your dance partner if they request it.
